# SECRET TEMPLATE -- DO NOT apply directly. Use kubectl command below.
#
# This file documents the required secrets for the run-api dev deployment.
# It is NOT a valid Kubernetes manifest -- use the kubectl command at the bottom.
#
# Secret Keys (12 total):
#
#   DATABASE_URL              - Async DB connection string (postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@host:5432/db)
#   DATABASE_URL_SYNC         - Sync DB connection string  (postgresql+psycopg2://user:pass@host:5432/db)
#   ZITADEL_ISSUER            - ZITADEL OIDC issuer URL (e.g. https://auth.civpulse.org)
#   ZITADEL_PROJECT_ID        - ZITADEL project ID
#   ZITADEL_SERVICE_CLIENT_ID     - ZITADEL service account client ID
#   ZITADEL_SERVICE_CLIENT_SECRET - ZITADEL service account client secret
#   ZITADEL_SPA_CLIENT_ID     - ZITADEL public SPA OIDC client ID (served to browser)
#   S3_ENDPOINT_URL           - S3-compatible endpoint (e.g. https://r2.cloudflarestorage.com/account-id)
#   S3_ACCESS_KEY_ID          - S3 access key
#   S3_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY      - S3 secret key
#   S3_BUCKET                 - S3 bucket name (e.g. voter-imports)
#   S3_REGION                 - S3 region (e.g. us-east-1)
#
# ---
# Create the secret with kubectl:
# ---
#
# 1. Copy .env.run-api.secrets.example to .env.run-api.secrets and fill in real values.
#    IMPORTANT: .env.run-api.secrets must NOT be committed to source control.
#
# 2. Create the secret:
#    kubectl create secret generic run-api-secret \
#      --namespace=civpulse-dev \
#      --from-env-file=.env.run-api.secrets
